                "type": "text",
                "text": "Been a while.  It's not so complicated — until it is.\n\nTo a first approximation, you clone whatever object looks most like what you want.\n\nEventually, you'll find that what you meant was that you wanted a copy (independent slots) rather than a clone (inherited slots) at which point, you'll tend to keep a bunch of prototype objects around which have the defaults for everything.\n\nLater, as you start to have complex structures of objects, you'll learn that the right clone/copy semantics interacts with how shallow/deep you want things to be.  It gets messy, and the next thing you know, you're writing factory methods.  "
